<p><b>Torgut</b> (also known as <b>Torghut</b> or <b>Torghud</b>) is a dialect of the <a href="/wiki/Oirat_language" title="Oirat language">Oirat language</a> spoken in <a href="/wiki/Xinjiang" title="Xinjiang">Xinjiang</a>, in western <a href="/wiki/Mongolia" title="Mongolia">Mongolia</a> and in eastern <a href="/wiki/Kalmykia" title="Kalmykia">Kalmykia</a> (where it was the basis for <a href="/wiki/Kalmyk_language" title="Kalmyk language">Kalmyk</a>, the literary <a href="/wiki/Standard_language" title="Standard language">standard language</a> of that region<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup>).Thus, it has more speakers than any other variety of Oirat.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> It is better researched than any other Oirat variety spoken in China.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
