<li>Bulaγ-a (2005): <i><span class="Unicode">Oyirad ayalγu-yin sudulul</span></i><span class="Unicode">. Ürümči: Sinǰiyang-un arad-un keblel-ün qoriy-a.</span></li>
<li>Coloo, Ž. (1965): <i>Zahčny aman ajalguu</i>. Ulaanbaatar: ŠUA.</li>
<li>Coloo, Ž. (1988): <i>BNMAU dah’ mongol helnij nutgijn ajalguuny tol’ bichig: ojrd ajalguu</i>. Ulaanbaatar: ŠUA.</li>
<li>Gordon, R. (ed.) (2005): <i>Ethnologue - Languages of the World</i>. Fifteenth edition. Dallas: SIL International: <a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=xal" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Kalmyk-Oirat</a>.</li>
<li>Janhunen, Juha (ed.) (2003): <i>The Mongolic languages</i>. London: Routledge.</li>
<li><span class="Unicode">Sečenbaγatur, Qasgerel, Tuyaγ-a, B. ǰirannige, U Ying ǰe</span> (2005): <i><span class="Unicode">Mongγul kelen-ü nutuγ-un ayalγun-u sinǰilel-ün uduridqal</span></i><span class="Unicode">. Kökeqota: Öbür mongγul-un arad-un keblel-ün qoriy-a.</span></li>
<li>Svantesson, Jan-Olof, Anna Tsendina, Anastasia Karlsson, Vivan Franzén (2005): <i>The Phonology of Mongolian</i>. New York: Oxford University Press.</li>
</ul>
